## 5B — VKD3D-Proton (`keyvalues/vkd3d.env`)

VKD3D-Proton translates DirectX 12 to Vulkan.
Source or export these before launching Wine. DX12 games (e.g. Elden Ring,
Cyberpunk 2077) need these in addition to the DXVK config above.

```bash
# ── Pipeline library cache ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Splits DX12 pipeline compilation and caches the result between sessions.
# Same concept as DXVK state cache but for the DX12 layer.
# no_upload_hvv disables a slow upload path that wastes time on mobile VRAM.
export VKD3D_CONFIG=pipeline_library_app_cache,no_upload_hvv

# ── Shader cache directory ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Must be in writable PERSISTENT app storage — NOT /tmp (wiped between runs).
# The cache is megabytes in size. On first run it builds; every run after is fast.
export VKD3D_SHADER_CACHE_PATH="${CONTAINER_DATA_DIR}/vkd3d_cache"

# ── Disable hardware ray tracing extensions ───────────────────────────────────
# Adreno 7xx does NOT have hardware RT acceleration. If VKD3D attempts to use
# RT extensions it burns CPU overhead with zero benefit. Hard-disable both.
export VKD3D_DISABLE_EXTENSIONS=VK_KHR_ray_tracing_pipeline,VK_KHR_ray_query

# ── Worker threads ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VKD3D uses these for async DX12 pipeline compilation.
# 4 is the sweet spot on Snapdragon — enough parallelism without starving the game.
export VKD3D_WORKER_THREAD_COUNT=4

# ── No debug output ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
export VKD3D_DEBUG=none
export VKD3D_SHADER_DEBUG=none
```

