## 5C — Mesa / Turnip Driver

Turnip is the open-source Adreno Vulkan driver. It is significantly faster
than the stock Adreno driver for Wine/DXVK workloads because it exposes
Vulkan extensions that the stock driver does not.

Ship the latest community Turnip build `.so` in `assets/libs/` and extract
it to app data on first launch, then set these variables before any Vulkan
call (i.e. before Wine starts):

```bash
# ── Load community Turnip instead of stock Adreno driver ──────────────────────
export MESA_LOADER_DRIVER_OVERRIDE=zink

# ── Persistent shader disk cache (GPU ISA level) ──────────────────────────────
# Mesa caches compiled SPIR-V → native Adreno ISA here.
# Without this Mesa re-compiles shaders from SPIR-V on every launch,
# which doubles the cold-start shader stutter.
export MESA_SHADER_CACHE_DIR="${CONTAINER_DATA_DIR}/mesa_cache"
export MESA_SHADER_CACHE_MAX_SIZE=512MB

# ── Async compilation at the Mesa layer ──────────────────────────────────────
# Works in tandem with DXVK async. Both the translation layer (DXVK) and the
# driver layer (Mesa) compile asynchronously — two-layer stutter elimination.
export mesa_glthread=true

# ── Disable known slow paths in Turnip ───────────────────────────────────────
export TU_DEBUG=noconform

# ── No HUD or logging ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
export GALLIUM_HUD=none
```

