## 5D — Wine Optimizations

Add these to the container startup script before launching the Wine process.

```bash
# ── ESYNC (eventfd-based synchronization) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Wine's default synchronization uses CPU spin-wait loops, which waste entire
# cores doing nothing but waiting. ESYNC replaces this with Linux eventfd,
# which sleeps the thread until the event fires.
# Result: dramatically lower CPU usage in multi-threaded games (RDR2, GTA V, etc.)
# REQUIRES: ulimit -n 1048576 set below, or Wine will crash immediately.
export WINEESYNC=1

# ── FSYNC (futex-based sync — faster than ESYNC on modern kernels) ────────────
# futex2 syscall is faster than eventfd on kernel 5.16+. If the kernel is older,
# FSYNC falls back gracefully to ESYNC. Always set both — no downside.
export WINEFSYNC=1

# ── REQUIRED for ESYNC: raise open file descriptor limit ─────────────────────
# ESYNC creates one eventfd per mutex/semaphore. Games like Elden Ring need
# hundreds of thousands. Without this ulimit, Wine crashes on startup.
ulimit -n 1048576

# ── Disable Wine debug output ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Wine debug logging is surprisingly expensive — it serializes strings and writes
# to stderr on every API call. Disabling it saves 5–10% CPU in many games.
# NEVER leave this at a non-silent level in production.
export WINEDEBUG=-all

# ── Command stream multi-threading ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Offloads Wine's Vulkan command recording to a second thread.
# Effectively free performance — always enable.
export __GL_THREADED_OPTIMIZATIONS=1

# ── Hide Wine from game DRM / anti-tamper checks ─────────────────────────────
# Some games crash or refuse to start when they detect a Wine environment.
export WINE_HIDE_NVIDIA_GPU=1
export WINEDLLOVERRIDES="winevulkan.dll=n;d3d12.dll=n"

# ── Frame rate cap ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Prevents GPU running at 100% which causes thermal throttling that tanks
# average FPS. Set to the device's display refresh rate.
# 60 for most phones, 120 for flagship 120Hz displays.
export DXVK_FRAME_RATE=60
```

