## 5E — Container Init (`ubuntufs` startup / proot-distro init)

These must run inside the Linux container before any game process starts.
Do NOT run them on the Android host OS.

```bash
# ── Virtual memory map count ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default Linux limit is 65,530 memory maps. Many games (and DXVK's shader cache)
# need far more. Elden Ring alone can exceed 300,000 maps at runtime.
# Setting this too low causes silent crashes or "cannot allocate memory" errors.
sysctl -w vm.max_map_count=2147483642

# ── Swappiness ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Lower value = OS keeps game data in RAM instead of swapping to flash storage.
# Flash swap causes severe micro-stutter. 10 means "only swap under extreme pressure."
sysctl -w vm.swappiness=10

# ── Dirty page writeback ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Prevents the Linux kernel from stalling the game thread while writing dirty
# pages back to storage. Low ratios = frequent small flushes instead of rare big ones.
sysctl -w vm.dirty_background_ratio=5
sysctl -w vm.dirty_ratio=10

# ── CPU performance governor ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Forces all CPU cores to max clock. Without this, the governor ramps clocks UP
# too slowly after a scene transition burst, causing visible micro-stutter.
for cpu in /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu*/cpufreq/scaling_governor; do
    echo performance > "$cpu" 2>/dev/null || true
done

# ── GPU performance mode (Adreno) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Forces Adreno to run at peak clock.
# Works on rooted devices. On non-rooted, use Android's setSustainedPerformanceMode (see 5G).
echo performance > /sys/class/kgsl/kgsl-3d0/devfreq/governor 2>/dev/null || true
```

