## 5F — Wine Registry Tweaks (per-game Wine prefix)

Apply these via `regedit` into the game's Wine prefix. The container startup
script should apply them automatically if the registry key does not already exist.

```reg
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Wine\Direct3D]
"MaxVersionGL"="opengl32"
"VideoPciDeviceID"=dword:00001C82
"VideoPciVendorID"=dword:000010DE

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Wine\DirectInput]
"MouseWarpOverride"="force"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\System\CurrentControlSet\Services\winebus]
"Enable SDL"=dword:00000001
"Enable Udev"=dword:00000001
```

For DX12 games specifically, use these DLL overrides to load the native
VKD3D-Proton implementation instead of Wine's built-in one:
```
d3d12.dll=n,b    — native VKD3D-Proton d3d12, not Wine built-in
dxgi.dll=n,b     — native DXGI layer
nvapi.dll=       — disable NVAPI entirely (not present, wastes lookup time)
```

