## 5G — Android Wake Lock + Sustained Performance

While a game is running, acquire these from Android Kotlin/Java code:

```kotlin
// Keep CPU alive and clocked during gameplay
// Release this in onGameStopped() — failing to release drains battery
val wakeLock = (getSystemService(POWER_SERVICE) as PowerManager)
    .newWakeLock(PowerManager.PARTIAL_WAKE_LOCK, "GameNative:GameRunning")
wakeLock.acquire()

// Keep WiFi connection alive — prevents mid-game disconnection
val wifiLock = (getSystemService(WIFI_SERVICE) as WifiManager)
    .createWifiLock(WifiManager.WIFI_MODE_FULL_HIGH_PERF, "GameNative:GameWifi")
wifiLock.acquire()

// Request sustained performance mode — prevents thermal throttle
// This tells Android to keep clocks stable rather than boost-and-drop
if (Build.VERSION.SDK_INT >= Build.VERSION_CODES.N) {
    window.setSustainedPerformanceMode(true)
}
```

