## Part 6 — Additional Improvements

### 6A — Shader pre-compilation progress UI

The stock app has no feedback when shaders are compiling on first launch.
Users see a frozen-looking screen and force-quit the app, which destroys the
DXVK state cache and forces a cold-compile on the next launch.

Add a persistent notification or non-dismissible in-game overlay showing:
```
"Building shaders… 247 / 2,483 — This only happens once"
```
with a `LinearProgressIndicator`. Read the compile count from DXVK log output
or by monitoring the state cache file size growth. Dismiss automatically when
compilation finishes. This one UX change has an outsized impact on cache hit rate.

### 6B — Per-game profiles

Different games need different configs. Create a `ProfileManager` that stores
per-game overrides:

```kotlin
data class GameProfile(
    val appId: Int,
    val dxvkOverrides: Map<String, String>,
    val envVarOverrides: Map<String, String>,
    val winePrefixPath: String
)
```

Write to: `keyvalues/profiles/{appId}.conf`

Expose a "Game Settings" bottom sheet (long-press → context menu → Settings)
with controls for the most impactful per-game options:
- Resolution scale: 0.5x / 0.75x / 1.0x / 1.25x
- Async shaders: toggle
- VSync: toggle  
- Frame rate cap: 30 / 45 / 60 / 90 / 120 / uncapped
- DX version override: force DX9 / DX10 / DX11 / DX12 / auto
